// method that takes array of integers and returns new array with odd elements

// CASUAL

Take array of ints called arr
Create empty array called result

Iterate over elements in arr
If the index of the element in arr is odd, append it to result

Return result

// FORMAL

START

SET result = []

LOOP over arr
  IF arr[index] is odd
    result[index] = arr[index]

RETURN result

END